    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 266067.0,
      "end_time": 270466.0,
      "text": "So Planck&#39;s constant is extremely small; it&#39;s"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 270466.0,
      "end_time": 281100.0,
      "text": "6.626 times 10 to the negative 34th joule times seconds."
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 281100.0,
      "end_time": 282533.0,
      "text": "10 to the negative 34th?"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 282533.0,
      "end_time": 286566.0,
      "text": "There aren&#39;t many other numbers in physics that small."
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 286566.0,
      "end_time": 290000.0,
      "text": "Times the frequency -- this is regular frequency."
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 290000.0,
      "end_time": 293700.0,
      "text": "So frequency, number of oscillations per second,"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 293700.0,
      "end_time": 295433.0,
      "text": "measured in hertz."
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 295433.0,
      "end_time": 296814.0,
      "text": "So now we can try to figure out,"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 296814.0,
      "end_time": 299333.0,
      "text": "why did physicists never discover this before?"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 299333.0,
      "end_time": 303233.0,
      "text": "And the reason is, Planck&#39;s constant is so small"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 303233.0,
      "end_time": 307000.0,
      "text": "that the energy of these photons are extremely small."
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 307000.0,
      "end_time": 310366.0,
